answer_llm:
Modify your tool schema so that each tool has a top-level `"type": "function"` and a nested `"function"` object.

Use this format:

```python
get_weather_tool = {
    "type": "function",
    "function": {
        "name": "get_weather",
        "description": "Get the current weather for a specific city or generate fake data",
        "parameters": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "city": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "description": "The name of the city to get the weather for."
                }
            },
            "required": ["city"],
            "additionalProperties": false
        }
    }
}
```

This should fix the `400 Missing required parameter: 'tools[0].function'` error in Azure OpenAI.

